remixlab.bias.event

Class MotionEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • remixlab.bias.core.BogusEvent
      • remixlab.bias.event.MotionEvent
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Copyable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DOF1Event, DOF2Event, DOF3Event, DOF6Event

    public class MotionEvent
extends BogusEvent
    Base class of all DOF_n_Events: BogusEvents defined from DOFs (degrees-of-freedom).

    A MotionEvent encapsulates a MotionShortcut. MotionEvents may be relative or absolute (see isRelative(), isAbsolute()) depending whether or not they're defined from a previous MotionEvent (see setPreviousEvent(MotionEvent)). While relative motion events have distance(), speed(), and delay(), absolute motion events don't.
